    {
      "id": "PopularPost201514",
      "post_content": "Honestly, I think I am letting my Bais get the better of me with all these new wolf cards and all these new werewolf cards, but I honestly see this a 'viable' play with Werewolf cards. The Ability is \"Turn +1\" giving it more power then a turn 2 (though, I have to admit, it could be a bit better). Please remember people the Focus on a Werewolf deck is to STOP yourselves from using spell's and use abilities like this card.  \n  \n**Strengths**: 2/2 for ![1](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=1&type=symbol)![Green](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=G&type=symbol) is alright making it on par with most other creatures of that CMC already. \"![2](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=2&type=symbol)![Green](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=G&type=symbol) means that it can power itself up to 4/4 turn 3 AND get a Werewolf creature it's Transformation at the end of the turn, without sitting there and wasting a turn completely. Wolf support is rather poor outside of Tokens, so that doesn't give it much of a bonus.  \n  \n**Weakness**: 2/2 for ![1](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=1&type=symbol)![Green](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=G&type=symbol) is rather pricey for a \"vanilla\" card until you can boost it up to 4/4 and even then, it's uses are limited. It has none of the Werewolf type other then [H](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=H)... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Tsunaki",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost201514\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_post\">Honestly, I think I am letting my Bais get the better of me with all these new wolf cards and all these new werewolf cards, but I honestly see this a 'viable' play with Werewolf cards. The Ability is \"Turn +1\" giving it more power then a turn 2 (though, I have to admit, it could be a bit better). Please remember people the Focus on a Werewolf deck is to STOP yourselves from using spell's and use abilities like this card.<br/><br/><b>Strengths</b>: 2/2 for <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"1\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=1&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Green\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=G&amp;type=symbol\"/> is alright making it on par with most other creatures of that CMC already. \"<img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"2\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=2&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Green\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=G&amp;type=symbol\"/> means that it can power itself up to 4/4 turn 3 AND get a Werewolf creature it's Transformation at the end of the turn, without sitting there and wasting a turn completely. Wolf support is rather poor outside of Tokens, so that doesn't give it much of a bonus.<br/><br/><b>Weakness</b>: 2/2 for <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"1\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=1&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Green\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=G&amp;type=symbol\"/> is rather pricey for a \"vanilla\" card until you can boost it up to 4/4 and even then, it's uses are limited. It has none of the Werewolf type other then <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"H\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=H\">H</a>... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 201514)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '201514'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy57717\">Tsunaki</span>\r\n                                (10/3/2011 1:40:15 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\